on\nmagnetic moment at NLO, and fitting $L_1^{(1)}$ simultaneously to $\\sigma_{np}$\nand $\\sigma_{nd}$ at NNLO, yields $\\sigma_{nd} = 0.463 \\pm 0.110$ mb and $0.519\n\\pm 0.043$ mb, respectively, where errors are naively estimated from\nEFT($\\pi\\!\\!\\!/$) power counting. In addition, we discuss how Wigner-SU(4)\nsymmetry may alter the naive EFT($\\pi\\!\\!\\!/$) expansion of $\\sigma_{nd}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 27 Oct 2022 17:52:26 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 21 Mar 2023 21:03:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-23"}
